            <scopecontent id="aspace_56ae348707c1afee9e02d5e458eb4f68">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Correspondence, financial papers, photographs, and memorabilia make up the papers of Walter Langford Smith, a special student at the Yale Law School in 1905 and 1906. Included are sixteen letters from his father William Henry Smith (1850-1922), and several letters from friends, sixteen photographs of unidentified people, cards, receipts, and similar materials.</p>
